WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.510 --> 00:00:05.309
In A Song of Ice and Fire, Coldhands is a
strange, mysterious figure, with connections

00:00:05.309 --> 00:00:10.140
to the three-eyed crow, the children of the
forest, the Night’s Watch, and the Others.

00:00:10.140 --> 00:00:16.279
Who is he, and what is he? Let's have a look.
In Book 3, Sam and Gilly are attacked by wights

00:00:16.279 --> 00:00:20.850
north of the Wall. They’re saved by a “thin”
“gaunt” “man” who wears black clothes,

00:00:20.850 --> 00:00:25.550
rides a “giant elk”, and uses a huge
group of ravens to fight wights kinda like

00:00:25.550 --> 00:00:30.449
in that Hitchcock movie. He never gives a
name, but Sam calls him Coldhands for his

00:00:30.449 --> 00:00:35.170
cold, black hands. Coldhands takes Sam and
Gilly south to the abandoned Nightfort on

00:00:35.170 --> 00:00:39.769
the Wall, and we learn that he’s been sent
by the three-eyed crow to fetch Bran Stark.

00:00:39.769 --> 00:00:45.359
So in Dance, Coldhands leads Bran, Hodor,
Meera and Jojen, to the three-eyed crow, far

00:00:45.359 --> 00:00:49.299
in the north.
During this journey, Meera gets really suspicious

00:00:49.299 --> 00:00:54.159
of Coldhands. Cause he never really explains
who he is and what’s going on, he hides

00:00:54.159 --> 00:00:59.489
his face behind a scarf and a hood – he’s
also dead. He doesn’t eat or breathe or

00:00:59.489 --> 00:01:05.449
seem to sleep, his heart doesn’t beat. Coldhands
is a lot like a wight, the zombies controlled

00:01:05.449 --> 00:01:09.690
by white walkers. They’re both described
as “dead things”, “pale”, with “cold”,

00:01:09.690 --> 00:01:13.670
“black” hands. They’re unable to cross
certain magical wards. They don’t seem

00:01:13.670 --> 00:01:17.980
to feel cold. And Coldhands fears fire, which
we know kills wights.

00:01:17.980 --> 00:01:23.210
But in other ways, Coldhands is very different
to a wight. Wights have bright blue eyes, but

00:01:23.210 --> 00:01:28.160
he has “black eyes”. Wights are slow
and clumsy, but he’s agile. Wights don’t

00:01:28.160 --> 00:01:32.990
talk, but Coldhands speaks in a rattling
voice, with intelligence, even hints of emotion.

00:01:32.990 --> 00:01:38.600
Wights seem to have lost their humanity, but Coldhands still seems to be a person.

00:01:38.600 --> 00:01:43.620
And while wights work for white walkers, Coldhands
serves the three-eyed crow.

00:01:43.620 --> 00:01:49.000
So the three-eyed crow is actually Brynden
Rivers, or Bloodraven, a Targaryen bastard,

00:01:49.000 --> 00:01:53.270
ex-Lord Commander of the Night’s Watch,
a “Dreamer, wizard … greenseer”, and

00:01:53.270 --> 00:01:57.490
one hundred and twenty-five year old man,
apparently kept alive by his connection to

00:01:57.490 --> 00:02:02.810
the weirwoods and the magic of the old gods.
Bloodraven’s goals and motivations are shady

00:02:02.810 --> 00:02:06.880
and unclear, but he mostly seems to hang out
with the children of the forest, watch the

00:02:06.880 --> 00:02:10.819
world through the eyes of weirwood trees,
skinchange into ravens, manipulate events

00:02:10.819 --> 00:02:15.840
from afar – y’know – standard psychic
tree man shit. Some people think that Bloodraven

00:02:15.840 --> 00:02:21.109
controls Coldhands by skinchanging into him,
like Bran controls Hodor. Which might happen

00:02:21.109 --> 00:02:25.849
sometimes, but surely not all of the time
– Coldhands does seem to exist as his own

00:02:25.849 --> 00:02:31.340
person. So what keeps this corpse walking?
Coldhands seems to be connected to the old

00:02:31.340 --> 00:02:36.139
gods. Like the greenseers of the children
of the forest, he has power over animals.

00:02:36.139 --> 00:02:41.060
He keeps a group of ravens to scout and fight
for him, and he can speak with them – “underst[and]

00:02:41.060 --> 00:02:45.930
their quorks and squawks”. He rides a “giant
elk” and when it dies, Coldhands performs

00:02:45.930 --> 00:02:51.760
a little ritual for it, “murmur[ing] a blessing
in some strange tongue as he slit[s] its throat”.

00:02:51.760 --> 00:02:56.239
Maybe it’s the magic of the old gods that
animates Coldhands. We’ve seen zombies of

00:02:56.239 --> 00:03:01.200
ice, zombies of fire, zombies of stone, zombies
of necromantic science – why not zombies

00:03:01.200 --> 00:03:06.889
of nature, of the old gods? Maybe, just as
the Others resurrect wights with ice magic,

00:03:06.889 --> 00:03:12.389
and Thoros resurrects Beric with fire magic, Bloodraven resurrects Coldhands with nature

00:03:12.389 --> 00:03:15.900
magic. Coldhands
is just another kind of zombie.

00:03:15.900 --> 00:03:20.590
So that may explain what Coldhands is. The
next question is who Coldhands is, or who

00:03:20.590 --> 00:03:25.279
he was before his presumed resurrection. His
identity does seem to be important because

00:03:25.279 --> 00:03:30.259
Meera keeps asking about it, and Coldhands
refuses to show his face or say his real name.

00:03:30.259 --> 00:03:33.700
So who could he be?
Coldhands seems to have been a brother of

00:03:33.700 --> 00:03:37.889
the Night’s Watch. He calls Sam “brother”, and wears black, though as Meera points

00:03:37.889 --> 00:03:41.999
out, “Anyone can put on a black cloak”, so it’s not certain that he was with the

00:03:41.999 --> 00:03:47.040
Watch. Either way, for a while, a popular
theory was that Coldhands is Benjen Stark

00:03:47.040 --> 00:03:51.999
– Ned’s brother who went beyond the Wall
in Book 1 and never came back. Maybe Benjen

00:03:51.999 --> 00:03:57.409
was killed by white walkers and later resurrected
by Bloodraven as Coldhands. It was a pretty

00:03:57.409 --> 00:04:01.790
good idea, but earlier this year, Reddit user
_honeybird checked out the original manuscript

00:04:01.790 --> 00:04:05.809
of Dance with Dragons and found a note from
George Martin saying that Coldhands is not

00:04:05.809 --> 00:04:10.859
Benjen – so there goes that idea. Other
possible Watchmen include Will and Waymar

00:04:10.859 --> 00:04:15.239
Royce, black brothers killed in the Prologue
of Book 1. This is kinda trickier because

00:04:15.239 --> 00:04:19.920
we know Waymar and probably Will were turned
into wights by the Others, so for one of them

00:04:19.920 --> 00:04:24.150
to be Coldhands, Bloodraven or someone must
have somehow restored their mind after they

00:04:24.150 --> 00:04:28.690
were zombified, which is not something we've
ever seen happen, so it seems unlikely that

00:04:28.690 --> 00:04:33.419
Coldhands is Will or Waymar.
Coldhands was apparently killed “long ago”,

00:04:33.419 --> 00:04:37.750
and we’re told this by a two hundred year
old child of the forest, so Coldhands probably

00:04:37.750 --> 00:04:42.890
died years and years ago. One cool idea is
that Coldhands is Ser Duncan the Tall, the

00:04:42.890 --> 00:04:46.840
protagonist of the Dunk and Egg novellas,
set almost a hundred years before the main

00:04:46.840 --> 00:04:52.000
series. Dunk had a relationship with Bloodraven
– he meets him at the end The Mystery Knight and

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:57.600
escorted him to the Wall when Bloodraven joined
the Watch. Maybe Dunk joined the Watch himself,

00:04:57.600 --> 00:05:02.150
was killed beyond the Wall, and became Coldhands.
There’s no real evidence for this, though,

00:05:02.150 --> 00:05:06.950
and certain facts don’t fit, like, Dunk
is really tall and Coldhands apparently isn’t,

00:05:06.950 --> 00:05:10.510
Dunk seems to have died at Summerhall, not
beyond the Wall, and if Dunk joined the Watch,

00:05:10.510 --> 00:05:14.970
we’d have probably heard about it. So that
one probably isnt’t true either.

00:05:14.970 --> 00:05:18.850
Another theory takes us much further back,
and links Coldhands to the legendary Night’s

00:05:18.850 --> 00:05:22.600
King, a Lord Commander from eight thousand
years ago who apparently married an Other

00:05:22.600 --> 00:05:27.160
or a wight. This would explain how Coldhands
knows about the Black Gate – the Night's King

00:05:27.160 --> 00:05:31.210
ruled at the Nightfort and may have used the
Black Gate for secret sacrifices. But there

00:05:31.210 --> 00:05:35.610
are a few reasons why this theory doesn’t
fit either. Firstly, the Night’s King was apparently

00:05:35.610 --> 00:05:39.300
cast down by the wildlings and the Starks,
but Coldhands was apparently killed by the

00:05:39.300 --> 00:05:43.060
Others. Even if the wildlings and Starks
let the Night’s King live – which would

00:05:43.060 --> 00:05:47.460
be weird, because they apparently “obliterated
[his] very name from memory” – why would

00:05:47.460 --> 00:05:51.270
the Others kill the Night’s King? He’d
apparently been making sacrifices to them.

00:05:51.270 --> 00:05:55.650
And even if they did, that doesn’t explain
why the Night's King would survive as a sentient

00:05:55.650 --> 00:05:59.910
wight for eight thousand years, or why he'd
end up working for Bloodraven, or why he'd

00:05:59.910 --> 00:06:05.390
have power over animals, or anything really.
And eight thousand years is a long ass time.

00:06:05.390 --> 00:06:09.720
Could a body and mind survive that long? We
are told that “cold preserves”, but if

00:06:09.720 --> 00:06:14.280
Coldhands is so ancient it seems weird that
he’s never described as such. From the way

00:06:14.280 --> 00:06:19.300
he speaks and moves and fights, he seems pretty
bloody sprightly for an eight thousand year

00:06:19.300 --> 00:06:24.060
old corpse. George Martin has implied that
the Night’s King has not survived to the

00:06:24.060 --> 00:06:29.610
present day. So overall, it seems unlikely
that Coldhands is the Night’s King.

00:06:29.610 --> 00:06:35.000
One more theory is that Coldhands is a descendent
of the Night’s King and his blue-eyed bride.

00:06:35.000 --> 00:06:39.580
Human-Other hybrids have been hinted to exist.
But Coldhands doesn’t really seem like

00:06:39.580 --> 00:06:45.850
he's part-Other. Others are strange, “beautiful” creatures,
“a different sort of life” – but Coldhands

00:06:45.850 --> 00:06:51.710
is just a dead man. He hasn’t got blue eyes,
or an icy sword, or really any special features

00:06:51.710 --> 00:06:57.210
of the white walkers. Even if he is some hybrid,
that doesn’t really explain why his mind survives

00:06:57.210 --> 00:07:02.160
his death. Besides, the Night’s King’s
bride seems more like a wight than an Other,

00:07:02.160 --> 00:07:08.080
and can you imagine a zombie giving birth to Coldhands?
Would you want to? There’s all sorts of

00:07:08.080 --> 00:07:11.530
spooky magic shit you can speculate but at
the end of the day there’s just no strong

00:07:11.530 --> 00:07:15.380
evidence for this stuff.
So there are lots of really interesting possibilities

00:07:15.380 --> 00:07:19.040
here, but none of them are all that convincing.
It’s tempting to conclude that Coldhands

00:07:19.040 --> 00:07:23.100
isn’t anyone special at all, just some random
Night’s Watchman who was killed by the Others,

00:07:23.100 --> 00:07:28.250
then resurrected by Bloodraven, but if that’s
the case, why does Coldhands hide his face,

00:07:28.250 --> 00:07:32.230
why do the books keep drawing our attention
to the mystery of his identity? It really

00:07:32.230 --> 00:07:37.500
seems like there’s something going on here,
but for now, we simply don’t have the answers.

00:07:37.500 --> 00:07:42.250
We don’t know who Coldhands is, but we can
make a pretty guess at what he is – he may

00:07:42.250 --> 00:07:46.450
be a Night’s Watchman who was killed by
the Others then was reanimated with the magic

00:07:46.450 --> 00:07:51.710
of the old gods, probably by Bloodraven and
the children of the forest. Whoever and whatever

00:07:51.710 --> 00:07:55.870
he is, Coldhands is a really a cool character,
so hopefully we’ll see more of him when

00:07:55.870 --> 00:08:01.350
Winds of Winter finally comes.
